data.title: 💜🏡 PRINCE: The Minneapolis home featured in “Purple Rain” is opening to the public for the first time, and you can stay there + get an...
data.meta_description:
axiostwincities on May 1, 2024: "💜🏡 PRINCE: The Minneapolis home featured in “Purple Rain” is opening to the public for the first time, and you can stay there + get an exclusive studio session for less than $100/night. BUT: you’ll have to win a lottery to get in. 

HOW IT WORKS: The house is available on Airbnb as part of the company’s new “Icons” category, but interested users have to enter for a digital golden ticket that allows them to book. Over 4,000 tickets across the 11 “Icons” homes are available this year, per a release.

WHAT’S NEXT: The home will begin accepting visitors in August. Click the link in our bio for details on how to get in. 

Pictured: The bedroom in the Purple Rain house. Photo courtesy of Airbnb".
